<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-28T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-28T10:00:00-05:00" n="242" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">662.7131/65: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany (<persName corresp="#p_SFM1" type="from">Sackett</persName>) to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-28T16:00:00+01:00">May 28, 1932—4
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 28—1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>107. Your 57, May 27, 2 p.m. Handed note to <persName corresp="#p_BBW1">Bülow</persName> this morning. He expressed
                                keen disappointment and stated that he was not yet able to acquaint
                                me with the attitude of the German Government in the premises.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SFM1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Sackett</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>